args:
The group puts an end to Hypnos, forcing Harle
to flee and freeing the village from the Empire's
grasp. However, the guardian dragon Sylvia still
appears to be Harle's prisoner—but Melsa may
have a clue as to where she can be found.
This is Melsa's village—which means\nwe've returned from the space between\nworlds.
Hey, the Hypnos copy disappeared! Nice.
Now this IS incredible! You did battle with\nthe true form of Hypnos and lived to tell\nthe tale.
But alas and alack for you, Hypnos remains\nalive and well. ...Come forth, my glorious\ncopy!
Aw, hell! Did we REALLY not kill the real\none back there?
If beating it once isn't enough, then we'll\njust use the otherworld fragment again\nand head back to...
Once the power in an otherworld fragment\nis consumed, it disappears.
Aaah ha ha! How terribly disappointing!\nIt seems as if you've exhausted all your\noptions.
Now, Hypnos! Put an end to this miserable\nprince and his retinue of fools!
Maybe we weakened the real Hypnos\nmore than we thought.
In that case, it may have taken every bit\nof strength it has left just to make the\ncopy appear.
Ah, yes. I see. Thank you for the most\nthorough explanation.
In that case, Hypnos, I command you to\nwithdraw for now.
Soldiers, we're withdrawing as well.\nConvey the order.
The Empire is...leaving? Wait, then\ndoes that mean we...?
Yep. We kicked their butts. We WON!
How wonderful! ...Hmm? Whatever is the\nmatter, Your Highness?
I don't like this. Harle and his men are\nwithdrawing far too easily.
Perhaps he lost his nerve once he saw how\nweak Hypnos had become.
Oh, I'm so happy to find you all well!
Hmm... Well, I suppose we should just\ncelebrate the victory in front of us for now.
Ya got that right. And there's only one way\nto do it... PAAAAAARTY!
...So THIS is sylvan grub, eh? Bwa ha ha!\nI was expectin' bird food, but this ain't\nhalf bad.
Hey, save some for the rest of us!
...Melsa? What are you doing over here\nall by yourself?
Ah, {player_name}.\nApologies, but I find I don't do well\namidst so much hustle and bustle.
Heh. I suppose our group can be a little\nrowdy sometimes.
But is that the only reason you're alone?\nIt looks like something's bothering you.
If there's something on your mind,\nI hope you'll tell me and let me help.
I had a feeling that might be it, seeing as\nwe haven't found her yet.
And none of the villagers know anything\nabout it. It is as if she simply vanished\nwithout a trace.
It's got to be Harle's doing. Maybe he\nmoved her to a secret location.
He might be planning to use her as a\nhostage—which would also explain\nwhy he was so quick to withdraw.
Still, until she is found, our village will not\nbe truly free.
I'm sorry, Melsa. I may have worried\nyou unnecessarily.
But if Sylvia is being held captive,\nwe'll save her. You have my word.
Thank you. That takes a little of the weight\nfrom my heart.
If your opponent goes low, you go high.\nAnd you hold on to hope in even the\ndarkest of hours.
Sarisse! Were you spying on us?!
Rude! I'm not SPYING! ...I'm just listening\nfrom way back here where you totally can't\nsee or hear me.
Look, I was worried, okay? You had this\nweird, serious look on your face, and then\nyou just took off.
But let's get back to this whole ＂I'm not\nlike that＂ bit. Because you, Melsa, are\nthe freakin' BEST.
You're kind to everyone, you're attentive\nto their needs, and you're just a super\nsolid person all around!
I could never do that. People get on my\nnerves way too much.
But I've always kinda wished I COULD be\nlike that. ...Deep down, at least.
Of course, ya dolt! I mean, look at me!\nI'm so crude and insensitive, it's like\nsomeone brought a fart to life.
I just talk and talk and blurt stuff out\nwithout even thinking about how people\nmight take it.
Ugh! You see?! I just went and admitted\nthat in front of {player_name}!\nI should have kept my big yap shut.
True, you may have a coarse side, but you\nrealize and recognize it, and even have\nsome desire to improve.
I would say those are fine qualities indeed.
And much as you envy me, I find myself\ndesirous of you. How freeing it must be\nto simply say what you feel!
Well then, now you know how I feel.
Ha ha ha! Oh man, this is super weird.\nWe should just magically switch lives\nor something and be done with it.
Heh. I suppose it IS a little odd.
It's good to see you smile, Melsa.
And to make sure you stay happy, we need\nto go after Harle and Sylvia.
Yes? Did you think of something?
...But I might have an idea as to where\nthis Harle character might be hiding.
Er, but I'm not positive! So we don't need\nto waste our time with a search if—
Melsa, if you think he's hiding somewhere,\nthen we are TOTALLY checking it out!
Sarisse is right. Besides, your hunch is\nall we have at the moment.
